Jackknife Estimates of Indirect Effect in a Simple Mediation Model for Data Generated from a Multivariate Normal Distribution

Source: R/jack_mcar.R
mvn_jack_mcar.Rd

Jackknife Estimates of Indirect Effect in a Simple Mediation Model for Data Generated from a Multivariate Normal Distribution

mvn_jack_mcar(data, taskid)

Arguments

data

n by 3 matrix or data frame. data[, 1] correspond to values for x. data[, 2] correspond to values for m. data[, 3] correspond to values for y.
taskid

Numeric. Task ID.

See also

Other jackknife functions: .jack(), mvn_jack_mar_simulation(), mvn_jack_mar_task(), mvn_jack_mar(), mvn_jack_mcar_simulation(), mvn_jack_mcar_task(), mvn_jack_simulation(), mvn_jack_task(), mvn_jack(), mvn_std_jack_simulation(), mvn_std_jack_task(), mvn_std_jack()

Examples

taskid <- 1
data <- mvn_dat(taskid = taskid)
mvn_jack_mcar(data = data, taskid = taskid)
